INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1645, 'How many ducks would there be, if you saw two ducks in front of two ducks, two ducks between two ducks, and two ducks behind two ducks? Answer: 4 ducks-because they are in a row.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1646, 'A couple of pigeons made a date to meet on the ledge outside the tenth floor of a skyscraper. The female was there on time, but the male arrived an hour late. "Where were you? I was worried sick.""It was such nice day, I decided to walk."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1647, '"Look at that speed!" said one hawk to another as the jet fighter plane hurtled over their heads."Hmph!" snorted the other. "You would fly fast too if your tail was on fire!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1648, 'Good news! I''ve been given a goldfish for my birthday. . .the bad news is that I don''t get the bowl until my next birthday!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1649, 'The housewife answered a knock on the door and found a total stranger standing on the doorstep. "Excuse me for disturbing you, ma''am," he said politely, "but I pass your house every morning on my way to work, and I''ve noticed that every day you appear to be hitting your son on the head with a loaf of bread.""That''s right." "Every day you hit him on the head with a loaf of bread, and yet this morning you were beating him with a chocolate cake." "Well, today is his birthday."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1650, 'Fred: Have you noticed that your mother smells a bit funny these days? Harry: No. Why? Fred: Well, your sister told me she was giving her a bottle of toilet water for her birthday.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1651, 'Fred: I was going to buy you a handkerchief for your birthday. Harry: That was a kind thought. But why didn''t you? Fred: I couldn''t find one big enough for your nose.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1652, 'I''d like to say something nice about you as it''s your birthday. Why don''t you? Because I can''t think of a single thing to say!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1653, 'A kindly old lady came across a little boy sitting on the pavement crying his eyes out. ''What''s the matter?'' she asked. ''It''s my birthday!'' he hollered. ''And I had a bicycle and a new tracksuit and this afternoon there''s to be a party with crisps and jelly and a birthday cake and a disco afterwards. . .'' and he had to stop talking because he was crying so hard. ''But that''s lovely,'' said the old lady. ''Why are you crying?'' ''Because I''m lost!''');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1654, 'What did you get for your birthday? Another year!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1655, 'When is your birthday? 17th January. What year? Every year!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1656, 'Sam''s girlfriend''s birthday was the same day as his father''s. He bought his girlfriend a bottle of perfume and his father a pistol. He wrapped the perfume and wrote a note to his girlfriend, saying, ''Use this all over yourself and think of me.'' Unfortunately he put the note on his father''s present.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1657, 'Something happened to me yesterday that will never, ever, happen to me again. How can you be so sure? I was 10 years old yesterday.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1658, 'How old were you on your last birthday? Eight. And how old will you be on your next birthday? Ten. Oh, I don''t think that''s possible. Oh, yes it is - I''m nine today.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1659, 'Grandma, is it exciting being 99? It certainly is! If I wasn''t 99 I''d be dead.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1660, 'I forgot my brother''s birthday last month. What did he say? Rick: Nothing, yet.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1661, 'Will you come to my party on Saturday? Yes, please, What''s the address? 25 The High Street. Just push the bell with your elbow. Why with my elbow? Well, you won''t be empty-handed, will you!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1662, 'I''ve been shopping for my wife''s birthday present. What did you get her? A bottle of expensive toilet water. It cost 20. 20! Why didn''t you come to my house - you could have had some of ours for free!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1663, 'Dad bought Mum a bone-china tea set for her birthday. How lovely!Yes, but he only did it so as not to have to do the washing-up. Mum''s too frightened he''ll break it!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1664, 'What''s the greatest birthday present? Hard to say - but a drum takes a lot of beating.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1665, 'What did the burglar give his wife for her birthday? A stole.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1666, 'Fred: I was going to buy you a handkerchief for your birthday. Betty: That was a kind thought. But why didn''t you? Fred: I couldn''t find one big enough for your nose.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1667, 'Fred: Do you like the dictionary I bought you for your birthday? Harry: Sure. It''s a great present but I just can''t find the words to thank you enough.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1668, 'A man who forgets his wife''s birthday is certain to get something to remember her by.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1669, 'BoyFriend: Why didn''t you give me anything for my birthday?GirlFriend: You told me to surprise you.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1670, 'A St. Louis mother telephoned the capital building over in Jefferson City and asked to speak to the game warden. After being switched from office to office, a voice finally said, "Hello." "Are you the game warden?" she asked. "Yes." "Finally Ah''ve got the right person!" she said. "Could yaw''l gimme some help with my son''s birthday party?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1671, '"I remember when the candle shop burned down. Everyone stood around singing ''Happy Birthday.''"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1672, '"Artificial intelligence is a wonderful thing.I told my computer that today is my birthday,and it said that I needed an upgrade."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1673, 'Joe was sitting at a bar. He was totally depressed. The bartender, serving him a drink, asked what was wrong."I''ll never understand women" said Joe. "The other night on my birthday, my wife said as my gift, I could do with her what I wanted.""Wow! That''s quite some gift" said the bartender. "So why are you so dejected?""Well I thought about it for a while" said Joe, "and decided to send her home to her mother, and now she won''t even speak to me!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1674, 'It was Grandpa Jones'' 100th birthday and he was still in perfect health. At his birthday party he was asked how he managed to live so long and stay so fit.He explained "I put my long life down to spending so much time out of doors. I''ve been in the open air, day after day, rain or shine, for the last 75th years.""How do you manage to keep up such a rigorous fitness regime?" we asked."It''s simple" he said. "When I married my wife 75 years ago, we both made solemn pledge on our wedding night. We agreed that whenever we ever had a fight, whoever was proved wrong would go outside and take long walk."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1675, 'What is your favourite type of birthday present? Another present!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1676, 'What did the birthday balloon say to the pin? "Hi, Buster."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1677, 'How does Moby Dick celebrate his birthday?He has a whale of a party!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1678, 'Why did you hit your birthday cake with a hammer? Because you said it was pound cake!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1679, 'What did one candle say to the other?"Don''t birthdays burn you up?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1680, 'Why couldn''t prehistoric man send birthday cards? The stamps kept falling off the rocks!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1681, 'Why did Davy Crockett always wear a coonskin cap? It was a birthday present from his wife!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1682, 'Where do you find a birthday present for a cat? In a cat-alogue!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1683, '"I guess I didn''t get my birthday wish." "How do you know?" "You''re still here!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1684, 'Why did the boy put candles on the toilet? He wanted to have a birthday potty!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1685, 'What do you give a nine-hundred-pound gorilla for his birthday? I don''t know, but you''d better hope he likes it!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1686, 'What song should you sing to a wildebeest on his birthday? "Happy Birthday To Gnu!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1687, '"Doctor, I get heartburn every time I eat birthday cake." "Next time, take off the candles."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (1688, '"Did you go shopping for my birthday present?" "Yeah, and I found the perfect thing." "What thing is that?" "Nothing!"');
