INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3373, 'Bill: Where did you get that gold watch Joe?Joe: I won it in a race. Bill: How many people participated in it? Joe: Three, a policeman, the owner of the watch, and me!!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3374, 'Late one night, a burglar broke into a house he thought was empty. He tiptoed through the living room but suddenly he froze in his tracks when he heard a loud voice say, "Jesus is watching you!" Silence returned to the house, so the burglar crept forward again. "Jesus is watching you," the voice boomed again. The burglar stopped dead again. He was frightened.Frantically, he looked all around. In a dark corner, he spotted a bird cage and in the cage was a parrot. He asked the parrot: "Was that you who said Jesus is watching me?""Yes," said the parrot.The burglar breathed a sigh of relief and asked the parrot: "What''s your name?""Clarence," said the bird."That''s a dumb name for a parrot," sneered the burglar. "What idiot named you Clarence?"The parrot said, "The same idiot who named the Rottweiller Jesus."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3375, 'What animals are poor dancers?Four-legged ones, because they have two left feet.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3376, 'What dance did the Pilgrims do?The Plymouth Rock.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3377, 'What dance do hippies hate?A square dance.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3378, 'What dance do you do when summer is over?Tango (tan go).');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3379, 'What is the difference between a dancer and a duck?One goes quick on her beautiful legs, the other goes quack on her beautiful legs.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3380, 'What kind of dance do buns do?Abundance.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3381, 'Why did the little kid dance on the jar of jam?Because the top said, "Twist to open."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3382, 'What did the overweight ballet dancer perform ?The dance of the sugar plump fairy !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3383, 'What sort of dance do fish do at parties ?The conga !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3384, 'What do you call someone who dances on cars ?A morris dancer !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3385, 'What do you get if you cross an insect and a dance ?A cricket ball !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3386, 'Where can you dance in California? San Frandisco.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3387, 'I''ve been invited to an avoidance. An avoidance? What''s that? It''s a dance for people who hate each other.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3388, 'How do you make a tissue dance ?Put a little boogie in it !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3389, 'Who is tall, dark and a great dancer ?Dark Raver !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3390, 'Q. What is good for your soul but not your soles?A. Linedancing!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3391, 'How do you see that a linedancer came from Belgium and not from the Netherlands?He wears the cardboard box on his boots.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3392, 'An avid line dancing couple go to the doctor for a check up because they are having trouble remembering anything but, all the latest line dances. The doctor finds them in excellent health (of course), but suggests that writing things down may help their memories off the dance floor. That night the husband gets up to go the kitchen and the wife asks for a dish of ice cream, suggesting that maybe he write it down. He says "I don''t need to write it down" She says "Well I want Strawberries on it, so maybe you better write it down" "I don"t need to write it down" He says and walks off in a huff. Twenty minutes later he comes back with a plate of bacon and eggs. "I told you to write it down" she says, "You forgot my toast".');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3393, 'Which dances do the burgers do best?The burger-loo and the char char!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3394, 'Why don''t dogs make good dancers ?Because they have two left feet !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3395, 'What do baby swans dance to ? Cygnet-ure-tunes !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3396, 'What''s a vampire''s favorite dance? The Vaults.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3397, 'Why did the two knives go to the dance together?Because they both looked sharp!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3398, 'These two friends are about to go to a club. One of them has a wooden eye. He said ''''If someone says something about my eye, i''m gonna snap.'''' They get there, and he asks a girl to dance. She says, ''''Would I?''''');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3399, 'Q. What do you call a line dancer on a cruise?A. An Ocean "Liner"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3400, 'There was a dance teacher who talked of a very old dance called the Politician. "All you have to do" she told her class "is take three steps forward, two steps backward, then side-step side-step and turn around."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3401, 'What is a frog''s favorite dance? The Lindy Hop.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3402, 'What is a duck''s favorite dance ? The quackstep !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3403, 'Which dance will a chicken not do ? The foxtrot !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3404, 'Q. What do tired line dancers do?A. They Line Down :-)');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3405, 'My dance partner dumped me for my best friend.Why? Was he a better dancer?Don''t know, I never met him.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3406, 'What do cars do at the disco?Brake dance.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3407, 'What do cows like to line dance to ?Any kind of moosic you like !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3408, 'Q. What''s the difference between a line dance instructor and a dentist? A. A dentist lets you sit down while he hurts you.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3409, 'Q. How many line dance instructors does it take to change a light bulb? A. Five!...Six!...Seven!...Eight!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3410, 'What lies on the ground 100 feet up in the air and smells? A dead centipede.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3411, 'What is the difference between a musician and a dead body? One composes and the other decomposes.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3412, 'What has four legs, a tail, whiskers and flies? A dead cat.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3413, 'What do you call a man who has been dead and buried for thousands of years? Pete.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3414, 'What''s a zombie''s favorite pop song? Dead sails in the sunset.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3415, 'What do you find in a zombie''s veins? Dead blood corpuscles.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3416, 'Where do ghosts go for their holidays? The Dead Sea.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3417, 'First ghoul: You don''t look too well today. Second ghoul: No, I''m dead on my feet.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3418, 'Did you hear about the man who left his job at the mortuary? It was a dead end job.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3419, 'Did you hear about the two men who were cremated at the same time? It was a dead heat.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3420, 'If a man was born in England, raised in America and died in Spain, what does that make him? Dead.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3421, 'Doctor, doctor, I feel dead from the waist down. I''ll arrange for you to be halfburied.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3422, 'Waiter, waiter! There''s a dead fly in my soup. Oh no! Who''s going to look after his family?');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3423, 'Why did the monster take a dead man for a drive in his car? Because he was a car-case.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3424, 'Teacher: If I had ten flies on my desk, and I swatted one, how many flies would be left?Girl: One - the dead one!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3425, 'Did you hear about the do-it-yourself funeral? They just loosen the earth and you sink down by yourself.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3426, 'Did you hear about the undertaker who buried someone in the wrong place and was sacked for the grave mistake?');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3427, 'Why do you want to be buried at sea? Because my wife says she wants to dance on my grave.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3428, 'I was so sorry to hear you buried your mother last week.Well, we had to, you know, she was dead.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3429, 'A monster and a zombie went into the undertaker''s. "I''d like to order a coffin for a friend of mine who has just died," said the monster. "Certainly, sir," said the undertaker, "but there was really no need to bring him with you."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3430, 'Did you hear someone has invented a coffin that just covers the head?It''s for people like you who''re dead from the neck up!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3431, 'The man who was about to die said to the Sheriff, "Say, do I really have to die swinging from a tree?" "Course not," replied the Sheriff. "We just put the rope round your neck and kick the horse away. After that it''s up to you."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3432, 'A chemist, a shopkeeper and a teacher were sentenced to death by firing squad. The chemist was taken from his cell and as the soldiers took aim he shouted "Avalanche!" The soldiers panicked and in the confusion the chemist escaped. The shopkeeper was led out next. As the soldiers took aim he shouted "Flood!" and escaped. The teacher was then lead out. The squad took aim and the teacher, remenbering how the other two had escaped, shouted "Fire!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3433, 'At the inquest into her husband''s death by food poisoning Mrs Wally was asked by the coroner if she could remember her husband''s last words. "Yes," she replied. "He said ''I don''t know how that shop can make a profit from selling this salmon at only 20 cents a tin..."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3434, 'A man is calling on his best friend to pay a condolence call the day after the friend''s wife has died. When he knocks on the door, he gets no answer, so he decides to go in and see if everything is all right. Upon entering the house, the man discovers his friend in the living room kissing a mate."Jack", says the man, "Your wife just died yesterday!!" His friend looks up and says, "In this grief, do you think I know what I''m doing?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3435, '"Why are you crying Fred?" asked the teacher. "''Cos my parrot died last night. I washed it in Wisk. . ." "Fred," said the teacher. "You must have known that Wisk''s bad for parrots.""Oh it wasn''t the Wisk that killed it, sir. It was the tumble drier."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3436, 'Doctor, doctor, I''m at death''s door! Don''t worry, Mrs Jenkins. An operation will soon pull you through.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3437, 'What kind of ghosts haunt operating theatres? Surgical spirits.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3438, 'How do you make a Venetian blind?Poke him in the eye');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3439, 'My brother''s a professional boxer. Heavyweight ?No, featherweight. He tickles his opponents to death !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3440, 'A monster and a zombie went into a funeral home. ''I''d like to order a coffin for a friend of mine who has just died,'' said the monster. ''Certainly ma''am,'' said the undertaker, ''but there was really no need to bring her with you.''');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3441, 'If a woman is born in Italy, grows up in England, goes to America and dies in Baltimore, what is she?Dead.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3442, 'Vampire 1: "I once went so long without fresh blood that I nearly died." Vampire 2: "How awful!" Vampire 1: "Yes. Fortunately, I found some in the neck of time."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3443, 'I''ve been e-mailing William Shakespeare.William Shakespeare''s dead, silly.No wonder he hasn''t replied.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3444, 'What is the last thing you eat before you die?You bite the dust.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3445, 'What did the little kid do with the dead battery?He buried it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3446, 'What is posthumous work ?Something written by someone after they are dead !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3447, 'Why did the cowboy die with his boots on ?Because he didn''t want to stub his toe when he kicked the bucket !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3448, 'When a knight in armour was killed in battle, what sign did they put on his grave ?Rust in peace !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3449, 'Why was George Washington buried at Mount Vernon ?Because he was dead !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3450, 'What are you doing? I''m trying to call Washington! Oh, haven''t you heard? He''s dead!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3451, 'Waiter, there''s a fly in my soup !Yes, it''s the rotting meat that attracts them !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3452, 'Q: What is the definition of Death?A: When you stop paying taxes suddenly.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3453, 'Three weeks after her wedding day, Joanna called her minister. "Reverend," she wailed, "John and I had a DREADFUL fight!" "Calm down, my child," said the minister, "it''s not half as bad as you think it is. Every marriage has to have its first fight!" "I know, I know!" said Joanna, "but what am I going to do with the BODY?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3454, 'There was a great loss today in the entertainment world. The man who wrote the song "Hokey Pokey" died. What was really horrible is that they had trouble keeping the body in the casket. They put his left leg in....Well, you know the rest.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3455, 'A dying man smells his favorite oatmeal raisin cookies cooking downstairs. It takes all the strength he has left but he gets up from the bed and crawls down the stairs. He sees the cookies cooling on the counter and staggers over to them. As he reaches for one, his wife''s wrinkled hand reaches out, smacks his and she yells: "No, you can''t have those! They''re for the funeral!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3456, '"Do you believe in life after death?" the boss asked one of his employees."Yes, Sir," the new employee replied. "Well, then, that makes everything just fine," the boss went on. "After you left early yesterday to go to your grandmother''s funeral, she stopped in to see you."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3457, 'A chap went up to the counter in the library and said, "Have you got any books about committing suicide?"The librarian said, "Yes. Take a look over there, somewhere on the middle shelf."The chap came back a few moments later and said, "I can''t find any at all."The librarian replied, "Yes, it''s awful. They never bring ''em back!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3458, 'Teacher: What can you tell me about the Dead Sea?Pupil: Dead ?, I didn''t even know he was sick !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3459, 'A man is fibbing away about how great things are in his country. Finally, he starts describing the tall buildings in his country. "There is a building so tall, it took my friend Alex 72 hours to fall off it!" "Oh, my God!" says his friend. "Surely he must have died!" "Of course. He was without food or water for 3 days!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3460, 'An English guy was very ill and his son went to visit him in the hospital. Suddenly, the father began to breathe heavily and grabbed the pen and pad by the bed. With his last ounce of strength he wrote a note, dropped it, and died. The son was so overcome with grief that he didn''t remember slipping the note into his pocket. At the funeral, he reached into the pocket of his coat and immediately felt the note. He excitedly read it thinking it might be something he could recite during the service. It said: YOU WANKER -- GET OFF MY OXYGEN TUBE!!!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3461, 'This elderly Newfoundland fisherman is on his deathbed and summons his 3 sons to his bedside. "Well boys, the time is near, and when I pass I''d like to be buried at sea." So the boys agreed. A few days after his passing, the local front page read, "Local Fishermen Were Shocked Today When Their Nets Brought in Patrick McRay in a Coffin, 3 Shovels and the Bodies of His Three Sons... Funeral arrangements haven''t yet been made, however, it is believed all wished to be buried at sea."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3462, 'Phoning the florist to order some flowers for her lover''s funeral, woman was caught off guard when asked what message she wanted on the card. "Message?" she sputtered. "Well, I guess, ''You will be missed."'' Visiting the funeral home, she was pleased that her floral tribute had arrived but mortified that the card had her exact words: "I guess you will be missed."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3463, 'Question: What did the dead raccoon say in his will? Answer: "Leave it to Beaver."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3464, 'A man was sitting in the electric chair. The executioner said, "Look, I''m sorry but I''m going to have to throw the switch in a minute." The man said, "Do me a favor and throw it out the window!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3465, 'Why do cemeteries have fences around them?Because people are dying to get in.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3466, 'Dentist begging the patient: Could you help me? Could you give out a few of your loudest, most painful screams?Patient: Why? Doc, it isn''t all that bad this time.Dentist: There are so many people in the waiting room right now and I don''t want to miss the 4 o''clock ball game.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3467, 'Patient: "It must be tough spending all day with your hands in someone''s mouth."Dentist: "I just think of it as having my hands in their wallet."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3468, '"I am sorry, madam, but I shall have to charge you hundred dollars for pulling your boy''s tooth.""Hundred dollars! Why, I understood you to say that you charged only twenty dollars for such work!""Yes," replied the dentist, "but this youngster yelled so terribly that he scared out four other patients out of the office."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3469, 'What does the dentist of the year get?...A little plaque.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3470, 'Why did the dentist make a poor date with the manicurist?Because they fought both tooth and nail!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3471, 'How many dentists does it take to change a light bulb?Three. One to administer the anaesthetic, one to extract the light bulb, and one to offer the socket some vile pink mouthwash.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3472, 'What did the werewolf eat after he''d had his teeth taken out? The dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3473, 'Monster: Doctor, doctor, I''m a blood-sucking monster and I keep needing to eat doctors. Doctor: Oh what a shame. I''m a dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3474, 'Fred''s mother was on the telephone to the boy''s dentist. "I don''t understand it," she complained, "I thought his treatment would only cost me $20, but you''ve charged me $80." "It is usually $20, ma''am," agreed the dentist, "but Fred yelled so loudly that three of my other patients ran away!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3475, 'Nigel: You said the school dentist would be painless, but he wasn''t. Teacher: Did he hurt you? Nigel: No, but he screamed when I bit his finger.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3476, 'Why are you laughing? My dentist just pulled one of my teeth out. I don''t see much to laugh about in that. But it was the wrong one!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3477, 'As the judge said to the dentist: Do you swear to pull the tooth, the whole tooth, and nothing but the tooth?');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3478, 'Why was the man arrested for looking at sets of dentures in a dentist''s window? Because it was against the law to pick your teeth in public.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3479, 'Who has the most dangerous job in Transylvania? Dracula''s dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3480, 'I''m suffering from bad breath You should do something about it!I did. I just sent my wife to the dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3481, 'Dentist: Don''t worry. I''m painless.Patient: I''m not.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3482, 'Patient: Doc, what should I do with all the gold and silver in my mouth?Dentist: Don''t smile in a bad neighborhood.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3483, 'Patient: Hey, that tooth you pulled wasn''t the one I wanted pulled.Dentist: Relax, I''m coming to it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3484, 'Father: Don''t you feel better now that you''ve gone to the dentist?Son: Sure do. He wasn''t in.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3485, 'Cloyd went to a Charleston dentist complaining his gums had shriveled up and his teeth were falling out. After examining him, the dentist said, "Your mouth is really bad. Do you brush?" "Ah sure do!" replied Cloyd. "Everee single day!" "What do you brush with?" asked the dentist, "Preparation H," said the redneck.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3486, 'I thought, Miss Smith, that you wanted yesterday afternoon off because you were seeing your dentist?That''s right, Sir.So how come I saw you coming out of the movie theatre with a friend? That was my dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3487, 'At what time do most people go to the dentist?At tooth-hurty (2:30).');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3488, 'What did the dentist say to the golfer?"You have a hole in one. "');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3489, 'Why does a dentist seem moody?Because he always looks down in the mouth.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3490, 'Why do dentists like potatoes?Because they are so filling.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3491, 'What is a drill team?A group of dentists who work together.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3492, 'Why do people dislike going to the dentist?Because he is boring.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3493, 'What is a dentist''s office?A filling station.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3494, 'What do you call the Scottish dentist ?Phil McCavity !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3495, 'What do you call a dentist in the army ?A drill sergeant !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3496, 'What time is it when you have to go to the dentist ?Tooth Hurty !');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3497, 'Did you hear about the dentist who planted a garden?...A month later he was picking his teeth');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3498, 'What game did the dentist play when she was a child?...Caps and robbers');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3499, 'What does a dentist do on a roller coaster?...He braces himself');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3500, 'What did the dentist see at the North Pole?...A molar bear');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3501, 'What was the dentist doing in Panama?...Looking for the Root Canal');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3502, 'Where does the dentist get his gas?...At the filling station');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3503, 'Why didn''t the dentist ask his secretary out?...He was already taking out a tooth');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3504, 'What did the dentist say to the computer?...This won''t hurt a byte');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3505, 'What did the tooth say to the departing dentist?...Fill me in when you get back');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3506, 'Anyone know the six most frightening words in the world ??? "The Dentist will see you now."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3507, '"Open wider." requested the dentist, as he began his examination of the patient. "Good God !" he said startled. "You''ve got the biggest cavity I''ve ever seen - the biggest cavity I''ve ever seen." "OK Doc !" replied the patient. "I''m scared enough without you saying something like that twice." "I didn''t !" said the dentist. "That was the echo."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3508, 'While I was waiting to see the dentist, a woman came out of his inner office smiling. Nodding to me, she said, "Thank goodness my work is completed. I''m so glad to have found a painless dentist and one who''s so gentle and understanding too." When seated in the dentist chair, I related the incident to the doctor. He laughed and explained, "Oh, that was just my Mother."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3509, '"I came in to make an appointment with the dentist." said the man to the receptionist." "I''m sorry sir." she replied. "He''s out right now, but..." "Thank you." interrupted the obviously nervous prospective patient. "When will he be out again ?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3510, 'Patient: Doctor, I am very nervous. You know, this is my first extraction.Young dentist: Don''t worry, it''s my first extraction too.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3511, 'Dentist: There goes the only woman I ever loved.Assistant: Why don''t you marry her?Dentist: I can''t afford to. She''s my best patient.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3512, 'Dentist: Just let me finish and you will be another man after these cosmetic procedures.Patient: Okay doc, but don''t forget to send your bill to the other man.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3513, 'Dentist to parsimonious patient "No, we give no discount for empty spaces when cleaning and polishing teeth Mrs. Borde!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3514, 'Young Charlie to dentist''s sexy chariside assistant "Aha ! Are you the lady orthodontist ?".The lady replied "No, but I''ll straighten anyone''s teeth "');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3515, 'Young lady to father "Daddy, when I grow up shall I become a heart-doctor or a tooth-doctor " "Dentist" "Why father ?" "We have only one heart, but 32 teeth!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3516, 'Patient to Dentist: "How much to get my teeth straightened?" "Twenty thousand bucks" Patient heads for the door.Dentist to patient: "Where are you going?""To a plastic surgeon to get my mouth bent."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3517, 'Patient: How much to have this tooth pulled? Dentist: With pain $200 and without pain $100. Patient: Well, without pain it''s cheaper. Pull it WITHOUT pain.Without anesthesia neither anything, the dentist begins to extract the tooth, when the patient outcry: Aaaahhhhhhhh !!!!!Hey, WITH pain it costs $200 !!!, replies the dentist.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3518, 'What''s worse than having your doctor tell you that you have VD? Having your dentist tell you.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3519, 'A patient asked the dentist, if it wasn''t nasty to be all the day with the hands in someone''s mouth.The dentist answered "I just think of it as having my hands in their wallet."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3520, 'Gerald: "Have you ever come across a man who, at the slightest touch, caused you to thrill and tremble in every fiber of your being?"Mabel: "Yes, the dentist."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3521, 'believe that the members of the dental profession are the only men who can tell a women to open or close her mouth and get away with it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3522, 'Patient:Do you extract teeth painlessly?Dentis: "Not always, the other day I nearly dislocated my wrist');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3523, 'Papa, why is it that dentists call their offices dental parlors?""Because they are drawing-rooms, my son."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3524, 'Pardon me for a moment, please," said the dentist to the victim, "but before beginning this work I must have my drill.""Good heavens, man!" exclaimed the patient irritably. "Can''t you pull a tooth without a rehearsal?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3525, 'What to do you call an old dentist? A bit long in the tooth');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3526, 'A man went to his dentist because he feels something wrong in his mouth.The dentist examines him and says, "that new upper plate I put in for you six months ago is eroding. What have you been eating?"The man replies, "all I can think of is that about four months ago my wife made some asparagus and put some stuff on it that was delicious ... Hollandaise sauce. I loved it so much I now put it on everything --- meat, toast, fish, vegetables, everything.""Well," says the dentist, "that''s probably the problem. Hollandaise sauce is made with lots of lemon juice, which is highly corrosive. It''s eaten away your upper plate. I''ll make you a new plate, and this time use chrome.""Why chrome?" asks the patient. To which the dentist replies, "It''s simple. Everyone knows that ... there''s no plate like chrome for the Hollandaise!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3527, 'Dentist: "You don''t need to open your mouth any wider. When I pull your tooth I expect to stand outside."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3528, '"Did you get your money?" ask the wife of the dentist who had just return from the delinquent patient''s home."Not a cent," growled the dentist, "and worse than that, he insulted me, and gnashed my teeth at me!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3529, 'Q: Why did the dinosaur cross the road?A: Because the chicken wasn''t invented yet.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3530, 'Q1: What vehicle does T-Rex use to go from planet to planet?A: A Dinosaucer');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3531, 'Q2: What kind of materials do dinosaurs use for the floor of their homes?A: Rep Tiles');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3532, 'Q3: What did the female dinosaur call her blouse making business?A: Try Sara''s Tops');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3533, 'Q4: What is the head of an Italian dinosaur family called?A: Ptera Don');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3534, 'Q5: How do you ask a dinosaur to lunch?A: Tea Rex?');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3535, 'Q: What do you say to a twenty ton dinosaur with headphones on?A: Anything you want. He can''t hear you.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3536, 'Q: Why didn''t the T-rex skeleton attack the museum visitors?A: Because she had no guts!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3537, 'Q: What do you get when you put a bomb and a dinosaur together?A: Dino-mite.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3538, 'Q: What do you call a Blind Dinosaur?A: Do-ya-think-he-saurus.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3539, 'Q: What do you call a Blind Dinosaur''s Dog?A: Do-ya-think-he-saurus-rex.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3540, 'Q: What was the most flexiest dinosaur?A: Tyrannosaurus Flex.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3541, 'Q: Why did the Apatosaurus devour the factory? A: Because she was a plant eater!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3542, 'Q: Why did the T-Rex eat hamburgers?A: Because he is a meat eater!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3543, 'Why does a dinosaur have cracks between his toes?To carry his library card.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (3544, 'Why don''t more dinosaurs join the police force?They can''t hide behind billboards.');
