INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4629, 'Why don''t Jewish mothers drink?Alcohol interferes with their suffering.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4630, 'Q: Why aren''t Hindu and Chinese people allowed to play hockey?A: Because everytime they go into the corner they open up a convienent store.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4631, 'Q: Do you know why the new football stadium they built in Warsaw could not be used?A: No matter where you sat you were behind a Pole.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4632, 'Q: How do you know you''re flying over Poland?A: Toilet paper hanging on the clotheslines.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4633, 'Q: How do you take census in a Polish village?A: Roll a quarter down the street, count the legs, divide by two, and subtract one for the Jew who catches it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4634, 'Q: Why do Polish hate Cauchy''s dog? (hint on Cauchy-Riemann theorem)A: Because it leaves residues at each Pole.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4635, 'Q: Did you hear about the Polak who thought his wife was trying to kill him?A: On her dressing table he found a bottle of "Polish Remover".');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4636, 'Q: Did you hear about the Polak who married an Amish woman?A: He drove her buggy.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4637, '"Where''s your pencil, Bud?" the teacher asked an American boy who had just come to school in Britain. "I ain''t got one, Sir." "You''re in England.now, Bud. Not ain''t, haven''t. I haven''t got a pencil. You haven''t got a pencil. They haven''t got a pencil.""Gee!" said Bud. "Pop said things were tough in this country, but I didn''t know pencils were so hard to come by."');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4638, 'An American tourist was visiting a quaint country village, and got talking to a farmer in the local pub. "And have you lived here all your life, Sir?" asked the American. "Not yet, m''dear," said the farmer wisely.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4639, 'An Irishman joined the American Air Force and was making his first parachute jump. The instructor said, "When you jump out of the plane, shout Geronimo and pull the ripcord." When the Irishman woke up in hospital a few days later the first thing he said was, "What was the name of that Indian again?"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4640, 'What do you call an American with a lavatory on his head ?John.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4641, 'Q: How do you tell which is the Groom at a Polish wedding?A: He''s the one with the CLEAN bowling shirt.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4642, 'Q: How many French farmers does it take to change a lightbulb ? A: Three. Farmer #1 goes away and gets a new lightbulb. Farmer #2 notices that it has been imported from Britain and promptly sets fire to it, so farmer #1 has to go and get another one, and then farmer #3 changes it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4643, 'Q: How many Australians does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: One, but you have to pry him off the sheep first. A: Two - one to say "She''ll be right mate" and one to fetch the beers. A: 16. One to change the bulb and 15 to say "Good on yer, mate!"');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4644, 'Q: How many Canadians does it take to change a lightbulb ? A: Twelve. Four to form a Parliamentary study committee to decide how to solve the problem, one Francophone to complain that I didn''t translate this joke into French, one Native Canadian to protest that the interests of Native Canadians have been overlooked, one woman from the National Action Committee On the Status Of Women to say that women have been underrepresented in the process, one to go over the border to the Niagara Falls Factory Outlet Mall and buy a new bulb and not pay duty on it on the way back, one to actually screw it in, one to collect taxes on the whole procedure so the government can afford it, one to buy a case of Molson for everybody to drink, and one to drop the puck.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4645, 'Q: How many Canadians does it take to change a lightbulb ? Q: How many Canadians does it take to change a lightbulb ?');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4646, 'Q: How many Chinese Red Guards does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: 10,000 - to give the bulb a cultural revolution.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4647, 'Q: How many Chinamen does it take to change a lightbulb? A: Thousands, because Confucious say many hands make light work.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4648, 'Q: How many Englishmen does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: What do you mean change it? It''s a perfectly good bloody bulb! We have had it for a thousand years and it has worked just *fine*.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4649, 'Q: How many Ethiopians does it take to change a lightbulb ? A: Three. One to change it and two to squabble over who gets to eat the packaging.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4650, 'Q: How many Germans does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: Ve are asking ze qvestions here! A: Two, one to give the order that the bulb be changed and one to screw it in.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4651, 'Q: How many Iranians does it take to change a light bulb? A: One hundred - One to screw it in and 99 to hold the house hostage.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4652, 'Q: How many Ayatollahs does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: None-there weren''t any light bulbs in the 13th century.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4653, 'Q: How many Italians does it take to change a lightbulb ? A: Two. One to change it and one to sprinkle it with Parmesan.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4654, 'Q: How many retarded Italian gardeners does it take to screw in a lightbulb? A: One, but don''t expect results.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4655, 'Q: How many Poles does it take to change a light bulb?A: Just one, but you need 6000 Russian troops in case he goes on strike!');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4656, 'Q: How many Russian leaders does it take to change a light bulb? A: Nobody knows. Russian leaders don''t last as long as light bulbs. A: None, the old bulb is just suffering from a cold.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4657, 'Q: How many Russians does it take to change a light bulb? A: That''s a military secret.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4658, 'Q: How many Serbs does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: Two-one to shoot the old bulb out and one to screw the new one in.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4659, 'Q: How many Americans does it take to change a lightbulb ? A: Two. One to replace it and one to tell him it was burned out (in states that still have car-inspection laws.) A: Three. One to stand on the ladder, and two to carry enough light bulbs until one is found that isn''t defective. A: 250,000,000, one to change it and 249,999,999 to debate whether it it was politically correct.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4660, 'Q: How many Polish-Americans does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: 170. One to send the Never Fail Novena to the Cheektowaga Times for publication so St. Jude may grant the lightbulb request, one to say the Last Rites for the old lightbulb, ten volunteer firemen to break into the house and smash the old light bulb to bits, fifty to protest the abortion of the old lightbulb, ten to organize a lawn fete and spaghetti dinner at Our Most Holy Precious Blood of the Seventeen Martyred Saints R.C. Church to raise funds to buy a new light bulb (and the Monsignor a new pair of bowling shoes as a gift on St. Stanislaus Day), twenty from Chiavettas Catering to serve the food, twenty to run the Monte Carlo gambling tent, fifty to run everything else, one to go to Koplinskis Appliances to buy the light bulb, one to screw it in, five to say the Rosary as the bulb is being screwed in, and the Monsignor to bless  it.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4661, 'Q: How many Italian-Americans does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: I dunno exactly, but my brothers girlfriends fathers boss secretary''s sister''s next door neighbors'' priest''s cousin''s union shop steward''s uncle''s Knights Of Columbus club Seargant-of-Arms nephew''s best friend did it real cheap for me once.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4662, 'Q: How many Scotsmen does it take to change a light bulb? A: Scotsmen don''t change light bulbs, it''s cheaper to sit in the dark');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4663, 'Q: How many Oregonians does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: Six. One to screw in the lightbulb and five to fend off all those Californians trying to share the experience.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4664, 'Q: How many newsmen does it take to screw in a light bulb? A: Only one, but he''ll tell everybody.');
INSERT INTO jokes VALUES (4665, 'What is the most common educational degree in New Mexico?Kindergarten dropout.');
